SIMPLE: licentious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Licentious
<hw>Li*cen"tious</hw> <pr>(-sh⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>licentiosus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>licencieux</ets>. See
<er>License</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Characterized by license;
passing due bounds; excessive; abusive of freedom; wantonly offensive;
<as>as, a <ex>licentious</ex> press</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A wit that no <qex>licentious</qex> pertness knows.</q>
<rj><qau>Savage.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Unrestrained by law or morality; lawless; immoral;
dissolute; lewd; lascivious; <as>as, a <ex>licentious</ex> man; a
<ex>licentious</ex> life.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Licentious</xex>
wickedness.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Unrestrained; uncurbed; uncontrolled; unruly;
riotous; ungovernable; wanton; profligate; dissolute; lax; loose;
sensual; impure; unchaste; lascivious; immoral.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Li*cen"tious*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Li*cen"tious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lich</ent>⟦br⟧
